Title : Kansas City Actors Theatre
Text : '''Kansas City Actors Theatre''' (KCAT) is a non-profit theatre in Kansas City, Missouri.<ref>Kansas City Actors Theatre." Kansas City Actors Theatre RSS. N.p., n.d. Web. 28 Mar. 2014. <http://www.kcactors.org>.</ref>
Started in 2004, Kansas City Actors Theatre was founded in order to “challenge and enlighten the Kansas City community by producing classic and modern-classic plays using Kansas City theatre artists.”  The company presents a collection of plays that are integrated either over a season or in rotating repertory, in order to deepen the appreciation of each play.<ref>Kansas City Actors Theatre." Kansas City Actors Theatre RSS. N.p., n.d. Web. 28 Mar. 2014. <http://www.kcactors.org>.</ref> The theatre is also known to be a place for young local actors to obtain experience in a professional setting.<ref>Trussell , Robert. "Acting troupe fills niche in KC theater ." [[The Kansas City Star]] 2 June 2005, sec. Theatre: 31. Print.</ref> The artist-led theatre company often collaborates with theatre students from the [[UMKC Theatre]] .<ref>Trussell , Robert . "Putting a Focus on Actors." Kansas City Star 18 Feb. 2007, sec. Theatre: 16-17. Print. 
</ref><ref>Suh, Grace. "Kansas City Actors Theatre and UMKC Theatre join forces in Oh, What a Lovely War! ." [[The Pitch (newspaper)|The Pitch]]. N.p., n.d. Web. 14 Apr. 2014. <http://www.pitch.com/>.</ref> This Mission was exemplified when they were the first theatre company to run [[Lanford Wilson]]’s Tally Trilogy in repertory.<ref>Trussell , Robert . "Three From the Talleys." The Kansas City Star 1 June 2006, sec. Theatre: 31. Print. 
</ref>

In 2015, KCAT was awarded the [[American Theatre Wing]]'s National Theatre Company Grant.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/american-theatre-wing-announces-recipients-of-2015-national-theatre-company-grants-com-360948|title=American Theatre Wing Announces Recipients of 2015 National Theatre Company Grants {{!}} Playbill|website=Playbill|language=en|access-date=2017-11-29}}</ref>

KCAT uses professional actors in various performance spaces around Kansas City, Missouri.<ref>Kansas City Actors Theatre." Kansas City Actors Theatre RSS. N.p., n.d. Web. 28 Mar. 2014. <http://www.kcactors.org</ref>  Notably, KCAT has produced productions at the [[National World War I Museum]] ,<ref>Cook, Liz. "Journey's End digs into World War I with grace and wit ." ThePitch.com: The Leading The Pitch Site on the Net. N.p., n.d. Web. 14 Apr. 2014. <http://www.pitch.com>.</ref> H&R Block City Stage, and in [[Union Station (Kansas City, Missouri)]].  Many founders of KCAT are also professors at UMKC Theatre, including [[Tom Mardikes]] .<ref>Trussell , Robert . "Putting a Focus on Actors." Kansas City Star 18 Feb. 2007, sec. Theatre: 16-17. Print. 
</ref>

For a short period, starting in 2006, Kansas City Actors Theatre changed its name to “Actors theatre”, but the name returned to the original name shortly after.<ref>Trussell , Robert . "Putting a Focus on Actors." Kansas City Star 18 Feb. 2007, sec. Theatre: 16-17. Print.</ref>

